Shahzad et al. [83] also used diselenide and disulfide in the synthesis of isocoumarins 184. Stilbene-based carboxylic acids 175 were obtained in 87–100% yields from corresponding esters by using lithium hydroxide. Compound 175 and its analogues were cyclized to dihydroisocoumarins 183 in 50–97% and isocoumarins 184 in 81–99% yields using N-phenylselenosuccinimide (N-PSS). Because of the high cost of N-phenylselenosuccinimide (N-PSS), another methodology was developed by Shahzad and coworkers using diphenyl diselenide and [bis-(trifluoroacetoxy)iodo]benzene to synthesize isocoumarins 184. Optimization concluded that 10 mol% use of catalyst diphenyl diselenide gave desired isocoumarins in excellent yield as shown in Scheme 30c.

